example, the octet sequence 16 02 03 01 specifies
bank/shelf number 22 (hex 16), group number 2
slot number 3, unit/port 1. This object value is
commonly reported in SNMP Traps to identify the
product's location.
variables.name: ADTRAN-MIB::adProdPhysAddress

description: This object is the identifier of a DS1 Inter-
face on a managed device. If there is an ifEn-
try that is directly associated with this and
only this DS1 interface, it should have the
same value as ifIndex. Otherwise, the value
exceeds ifNumber, and is a unique identifier
following this rule: inside interfaces (e.g.
equipment side) with even numbers and outside
interfaces (e.g., network side) with odd
numbers.
variables.name: RFC1406-MIB::dsx1LineIndex

description: This trap indicates that the far end daily (total) interval Controlled
Slip Seconds threshold has been exceeded on the specified ds1 line.

event.Summary: Far end daily interval controlled slip seconds threshold exceeded on DS1 line $v2
